LOS ANGELES, Feb. 25 (Xinhua) -- Two bicyclists were killed and 11 others seriously injured after they were hit by a pickup truck Saturday morning in the southwestern U.S. state of Arizona, local media reported, citing police. The accident occurred just before 8 a.m. local time (1600 GMT) on the Cotton Lane Bridge in Goodyear, a suburb of Phoenix, the capital city of Arizona, according to azcentral.com, the digital home of The Arizona Republic newspaper. The truck driver stayed at the scene after the fatal accident, the Goodyear Police Department said in a news release. Officials said that an investigation is underway.  â– 